    <abstract id="aspace_93afa81f87abafc6580d52c7c9eab07f">Adam Purple (1930-2015) was an author, environmental activist, "guerrilla gardener," and a participant in the urban gardening movement that occurred in New York City's Lower East Side during the 1970s and 1980s. Harvey Wang is an American photographer based in New York City best known for his short films and portraits. This collection, which was created by Wang, focuses upon Adam Purple's time in New York City and is comprised of photographs taken by Wang; correspondence and petitions relating to Purple's Garden of Eden; flyers, posters, and news clippings about Purple; copies of Purple's written works; and an interview transcript from an oral history project Purple participated in with StoryCorps, a non-profit created to record and preserve the stories of Americans.</abstract>
    <physloc id="aspace_260b7e00857f0f7fc9b1931fee178134">Materials are stored offsite and advance notice is required for use. Please request materials at least two business days prior to your research visit to coordinate access.</physloc>
